<br>
On familiar...  I'd heard that invis killed 54 familiar, but I haven't found that to be true.  I routinely &quot;/pet get lost&quot; after summoning and after zoning, but neither abscond, gate, port, tl, nor invis have ever poofed my pet up to and through level 54 pet.  Only low health zoning (or absconding) has poofed pet, though it also poofed 7 other buffs as well.<br>
<br>
On spell gems popping too soon, it's not just first slot.  I have yaulp in slot 3 on two different characters and frequently get the message, though usually immediately after casting something else.  I also see this problem with tash on my chanter, regardless of spell slot.  I used to see this frequently on my pillars and circles, but I just got so used to waiting another half second that I don't notice it much anymore.  The fade-in time of the new ui also helps disguise the effect.<br>
<br>
Periodically we have spells become useless due to shifts in semantics for other related spells.  For instance, eye of tallon - does is really have any use now that aggro has been removed?  I suspect that this is what's happened to al kabor spells.<br>
