Another wierd thing: what is it with game companies writing everything from a female perspective?  The entire new version of D&amp;D assumes everyone is female, using female single pronouns such as &quot;she or her&quot; every example.  Now, most of humanity that speaks English, and in fact every female I talked to realizes that the generic use of &quot;he&quot; which has been in place for centuries means a generic &quot;human.&quot;  Using &quot;she&quot; in that place makes it female, and those same women felt wierd when they saw it, they said it breaks the flow of the sentance and makes you think its referring to a woman, not just any player or character.<br>
